  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed using a Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition variability (±8% flow rate, ±5% rotational speed) across 500 model evaluations, yielding a 95th-percentile relative hemolysis index of 0.87. A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally during model development to identify potentially influential parameters; results indicated that rotational speed and gap geometry were likely dominant drivers. These findings informed the UQ input distributions but were not formally encoded as a structured sensitivity analysis artefact.",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
