      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters must be documented with sources and uncertainty ranges; nominal values must be traceable to device specifications or experimental measurements.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) are documented with sources. Blood viscosity was set to 0.0035 Pa·s per ISO 10993-4 reference fluid. Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds were taken from FDA experimental protocol. Uncertainty ranges for key inputs were established and used as the basis for the Monte Carlo UQ study, which propagated inlet flow rate variability (±8%) and rotational speed variability (±5%) through 500 model evaluations. The screening sensitivity study conducted informally during model development identified these two parameters as likely dominant contributors to NIH variance, informing the choice of UQ input distributions."
    },
